---
title: Lemon Cream Chicken Cutlets plus a side of Dill Potatoes & Green Beans
description: If we were forced to choose a favorite food group, we just might pick sauce—we firmly believe it’s one of the best parts of any dish. That’s why we’re over the moon for this silky garlic-lemon version: It’s rich, creamy, tangy, and couldn’t be simpler to make. Just sauté garlic until fragrant, then stir in chicken stock, sour cream, and lemon juice for positively luscious results. It’s spooned all over chicken cutlets seasoned with warm, aromatic Shawarma spices. Pro tip: You’ll want to save a bit for dipping your sides of roasted green beans and dill potatoes, ‘cause there’s nothing this sauce can’t do.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/lemon-cream-chicken-cutlets-f0f3dedc.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/lemon-cream-chicken-cutlets-5ed50625b9b28c3b167dce3a-c81c3cdc.pdf
author: HelloFresh
time required: 40 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 480 kcal
  fat: 19 g
  saturated fat: 4.5 g
  carbohydrates: 44 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 420 mg
cuisine: Mediterranean
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/lemon-cream-chicken-cutlets-5ed50625b9b28c3b167dce3a
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}. Pick and roughly chop fronds from @Dill{1/4%ounce}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes}.

> Spread potatoes out across entire sheet for 4 servings.

Once potatoes have roasted 10 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully toss @Green Beans{6%ounce} on empty side with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

Return to oven and roast until veggies are browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes} more.

> Leave potatoes in oven and toss green beans on a separate sheet; roast on middle rack for 4 servings.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @Shawarma Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; remove chicken from pan. Wash out pan.

> Use all the Shawarma Spice for 4 servings. If spices begin to burn, reduce heat to medium.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, ¼ cup @water{1/4%cup}, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Bring to a simmer and cook until reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove pan from heat and stir in @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon} and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste.

> Use 1/3 cup water for 4 servings.

Toss roasted potatoes with half the dill and lemon zest to taste.

Divide potatoes, green beans, and chicken between plates. Top chicken with lemon cream sauce and sprinkle with remaining dill. Serve.